ZH: 我对自己的决定感到悔恨。
EN: I feel regretful about my decision.

ZH: 她在失去机会后充满了悔恨。
EN: She is full of regret after missing the opportunity.

ZH: 我对自己的过去感到悔恨。
EN: I feel regretful about my past.

ZH: 我深深地悔恨自己没有早点学习中文。
EN: I deeply regret not learning Chinese earlier.

ZH: 他悔恨地否认了自己的错误。
EN: He regrettably denied his mistake.

ZH: 她后悔已经浪费了这么多时间。
EN: She regrets wasting so much time.

ZH: 我感到深深的悔恨，因为我没有听从你的忠告。
EN: I feel deep regret for not taking your advice.

ZH: 它们充满了悔恨地向敌人投降。
EN: They surrendered to the enemy with regret.

ZH: 我悔恨没有趁机告诉她我对她的感觉。
EN: I regret not telling her how I feel when I had the chance.

ZH: 他对过去的恶行感到深深的悔恨。
EN: He feels deep regret for his past misdeeds.

ZH: 她对失去的机会充满了悔恨。
EN: She is filled with regret for the missed opportunity.

ZH: 我们应该学会从错误中汲取教训，而不是一直悔恨自己。
EN: We should learn from our mistakes instead of constantly regretting ourselves.

ZH: 他曾经做出了一些错误的决定，对此感到悔恨。
EN: He had made some wrong decisions and regrets them.

ZH: 她一直悔恨自己没有好好珍惜过去的机会。
EN: She regrets not cherishing the past opportunities.

ZH: 他悔恨着没有及时向她道歉。
EN: He regrets not apologizing to her on time.

ZH: 她对自己急躁的举动感到悔恨。
EN: She regrets her impatient actions.

ZH: 我悔恨当初没有相信你的忠告。
EN: I regret not believing your advice at that time.

ZH: 这次失败让我充满了悔恨。
EN: This failure fills me with regret.

ZH: 我悔恨没有好好珍惜和家人相处的时间。
EN: I regret not cherishing the time spent with my family.

ZH: 它们悔恨所犯下的错误。
EN: They regret the mistakes they have made.

ZH: 我们应该从过去的错误中吸取教训，而不只是感到悔恨。
EN: We should learn from the mistakes of the past, not just feel regret.
